body.title: How Autism Is Different in Boys and Girls Medical bias can sometimes lead to differences in how autism is diagnosed in boys and girls. Read

Study Says Birth Spacing Can Impact Autism Diagnosis A new study says that birth spacing after a child diagnosed with autism can impact whether the second child is also born on the autism spectrum. Read
Signs of Autism in Babies and Toddlers Signs of autism can be present in babies as young as several months old. Learn more about how to recognize signs of autism in babies and toddlers. Read
How Do I Get My Child Tested for Autism? The thought of having a child with autism can feel overwhelming at times. Getting your child diagnosed early will benefit both of you. Find out why. Read

Autism and Discipline: Strategies for Kids With Autism When parenting a child with autism, discipline can be a challenge. Provide consistent rules and routines and seek to understand your child’s behavior and needs. Read
Kids With Autism Twice As Likely to Consider Suicide Kids diagnosed with autism spectrum disorder are twice as likely to have thoughts of suicide, according to a new study. Read

No Connection Between H1N1 Flu Vaccine and Autism, Study Finds Many moms-to-be worry about side effects of the flu vaccine for their unborn babies, including autism. But a new study puts those fears to rest. Read
Signs of Autism in Infants and Babies In the past, children with autism spectrum disorder were rarely diagnosed before age 3, but many babies show signs as early as six months. Read
